      "text": "<b>Parallel wiki thread cleaning</b> is where you clean up a [[Thread Mode]] document by creating a parallel page with a similar name. The parallel document tries to convert the arguments in thread mode into a more compact or more organized form. When a consensus is reached that the new page captures the points of views in the threaded version, then the threaded version is eventually deleted, archived, or perhaps left in as a \"discussion\" section. Note that one should wait for discussion activity to die down first. It might also take several months before the replacement is ready. ",
